{"bookmarked": 8, "bucket_name": "Today", "bucket_order": 3, "change_log": [{"anon": "stud", "data": "kcy9qv57yce3du", "type": "create", "uid_a": "a_0", "v": "all", "when": "2020-07-23T04:01:29Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "kcy9qv54nug3dt", "type": "followup", "uid_a": "a_1", "when": "2020-07-23T08:05:58Z"}], "children": [{"anon": "stud", "bucket_name": "Week 7/19 - 7/25", "bucket_order": 19, "children": [], "config": {}, "created": "2020-07-23T08:05:58Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "kcyih9hnvk5ca", "no_answer": 0, "no_upvotes": 0, "subject": "<p>If you&#39;re interested in security, take 161/261 as soon as possible. Though note that Weaver (who&#39;s teaching it in Fall) really dislikes blockchain. Raluca usually teaches it in spring and she does a bit of research in decentralized systems (ie. blockchain) - but I believe she&#39;s actually not teaching this spring for some reason.<br /><br />Personally, I would recommend simply researching faculty and reaching out to them. You could also try applying through programs like <a href=\"https://dare.berkeley.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">DARE</a> or <a href=\"https://urap.berkeley.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">URAP</a>. I know multiple professors that select students from those places.</p>", "tag_good": [{"admin": false, "endorser": {}, "facebook_id": null, "id": "jzlnp0wt88i22b", "name": "Simon Guo", "photo": "1580315354_200.jpg", "photo_url": "https://d1b10bmlvqabco.cloudfront.net/photos/jzlnp0wt88i22b/1580315354_200.jpg", "published": true, "role": "student", "us": false}], "tag_good_arr": ["jzlnp0wt88i22b"], "type": "followup", "uid_a": "a_1", "updated": "2020-07-23T08:05:58Z"}], "config": {"seen": {"10580": 9, "11988": 1, "12070": 2, "12159": 5, "6403": 6, "7227": 4, "7246": 3, "7594": 0, "8111": 7, "8145": 8}}, "created": "2020-07-23T04:01:29Z", "data": {"embed_links": []}, "default_anonymity": "no", "drafts": null, "folders": ["cs-intended", "policy", "faculty_advising", "research", "enrichment_opportunities"], "history": [{"anon": "stud", "content": "<p>Hello, I&#39;m a incoming sophomore with good grades in all his classes. I haven&#39;t had much research experience and I&#39;m kinda lost in the whole process. Can someone outline me some steps I can do to get some research positions or prepare myself for that position. My interests are pretty varied and I&#39;ll be good with anything I can get. That being said, I am fascinated with computer security and blockchain and I&#39;m currently self studying pytorch.\u00a0</p>", "created": "2020-07-23T04:01:29Z", "subject": "tips on getting research", "uid_a": "a_0"}], "history_size": 1, "i_edits": [], "id": "kcy9qv54nug3dt", "is_bookmarked": false, "is_tag_good": false, "my_favorite": false, "no_answer": 1, "no_answer_followup": 0, "nr": 12737, "num_favorites": 1, "q_edits": [], "request_instructor": 0, "request_instructor_me": false, "s_edits": [], "status": "active", "t": 1654542995534, "tag_good": [{"admin": false, "endorser": {"kd0ifacummd56a": 1599633405}, "facebook_id": null, "id": "jzoqqipkxx270r", "name": "Animesh", "photo": null, "photo_url": null, "role": "student", "us": false}, {"admin": false, "endorser": {}, "facebook_id": null, "id": "k5k3fsp6g1u6lv", "name": "Dayne Tran", "photo": "1595720343_200.jpg", "photo_url": "https://d1b10bmlvqabco.cloudfront.net/photos/k5k3fsp6g1u6lv/1595720343_200.jpg", "published": true, "role": "student", "us": false}], "tag_good_arr": ["jzoqqipkxx270r", "k5k3fsp6g1u6lv"], "tags": ["cs-intended", "enrichment_opportunities", "faculty_advising", "policy", "research", "student", "unanswered"], "type": "question", "unique_views": 436}